<!-- Sign Up Page -->
<div class="signup-container">
  <div class="signup-card">
    <h2> <i class="fa-solid fa-user-plus"></i> Sign Up</h2>
    <p> Let's create your account. </p>

    <%= form_with model: @user, url: signup_path, local: true, class: "signup-form" do |f| %>
      
      <!-- First Name -->
      <div class="input-group">
        <label for="FName">First Name</label>
        <div class="input-field">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-user"></i>
          <%= f.text_field :FName, placeholder: "Enter your first name", required: true, class: "signup-input" %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Last Name -->
      <div class="input-group">
        <label for="LName">Last Name</label>
        <div class="input-field">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-user"></i>
          <%= f.text_field :LName, placeholder: "Enter your last name", required: true, class: "signup-input" %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Email -->
      <div class="input-group">
        <label for="Email">Email</label>
        <div class="input-field">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-envelope"></i>
          <%= f.email_field :Email, placeholder: "youremail@example.com", required: true, class: "signup-input" %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Password -->
      <div class="input-group">
        <label for="Password">Password</label>
        <div class="input-field">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-lock"></i>
          <%= f.password_field :Password, placeholder: "Create a password", required: true, class: "signup-input" %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Role Selection -->
      <div class="role-selection">
        <p>Please select your role:</p>
        <label class="role-option">
          <%= f.radio_button :Role, "Tenant", checked: true, class: "signup-radio" %>
          Tenant
        </label>
        <label class="role-option">
          <%= f.radio_button :Role, "Landlord", class: "signup-radio" %>
          Landlord
        </label>
      </div> 

      <!-- Disclaimer -->
      <div class="disclaimer">
        <label class="custom-checkbox">
            <%= f.check_box :ProfileDisclaimer, {}, 'yes', 'no' %>
            <span class="checkmark"></span>
            <span class="disclaimer-text">
                I have read and agree to the <label for="toggleModal" class="disclaimer-link">Terms and Conditions</label>
            </span>
        </label>
      
        <% if @user.errors[:ProfileDisclaimer].any? %>
          <div class="error-text"><%= @user.errors[:ProfileDisclaimer].first %></div>
        <% end %>
      </div>

      <!-- Hidden Checkbox to Toggle Modal -->
      <input type="checkbox" id="toggleModal" class="toggle-checkbox">

      <!-- Modal Popup -->
      <div class="modal-popup">
        <div class="popup-content">
          <!-- Clicking this label will uncheck the checkbox, closing the modal -->
          <label for="toggleModal" class="close-popup">&times;</label>
          <h4>Terms and Conditions</h4>
          <p>Welcome to the Franklin County Municipal Court Self Help Center and Dispute Resolution Program&apos;s online mediation platform. 
              Before creating a profile on this platform, please review the following statements. 
              By clicking “I Agree” at the bottom, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and accept the terms of this disclaimer.</p>
          <p><strong>1. No Legal Advice or Attorney-Client Relationship</strong></p>
          <p>This platform provides general information and mediation tools to help landlords and tenants communicate and potentially resolve disputes. 
              <strong>It does not give legal advice or representation.</strong> The information available on this platform does not replace advice from a qualified attorney.
              Use of this platform does <strong>not</strong> create an attorney-client relationship between you and any other person associated with this service. 
              If you need legal advice, you should speak with a licensed attorney.</p>
          <p><strong><a href="https://municipalcourt.franklincountyohio.gov/Departments-Services/Self-Help/Court-Basics#Lawyers-and-Legal-Help" target="_blank">CLICK HERE</a></strong> 
              for resources to help find an attorney, if needed. </p>
          <p><strong>2. User Responsibility and Reliance on Information</strong></p>
          <p>You are responsible for providing accurate information when using this platform. You are also responsible for verifying the accuracy of any 
              information provided through this platform. The platform is provided “as is” without warranties of any kind. Users assume full responsibility 
              for their participation. </p>
          <p><strong>3. Data Privacy</strong></p>
          <p>This platform is operated by the Franklin County Municipal Court Self-Help Center and Dispute Resolution Department. If you have any questions 
              about how your personal data is handled, you may contact them directly at &#40;614&#41; 645-7381 from Monday through Friday, 9 AM to 3 PM. </p>
          <p>Personal data collected through this platform is used to facilitate dispute resolution services, including scheduling mediation, communicating with users, 
              and documenting mediation outcomes. Additionally, your data may be used to help inform future policy decisions and ongoing refinements to the system to 
              improve its effectiveness and accessibility. Your data will only be shared with the Dispute Resolution Department and any mediators assigned to your case. </p>
          <p>Personal data will be kept for one year, as required by the record-keeping rules set by the Court. You can ask for access, correction, or deletion of your 
              personal data at any time. Additionally, you may withdraw your consent for data processing at any time; however, doing so may impact your ability to use 
              the mediation services provided. </p>
          <p>We implement security protocols to protect user data. Regardless, users should exercise caution when sharing sensitive information.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sign Up Button -->
      <%= f.submit "Sign Up", class: "signup-btn" %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
